# Task & TODO Tracking

## Session Start Protocol
At the start of every development session:
1. Read `5-Development-Status.md` (or the latest status reference) to understand current state
2. Review open TODOs and pending work items
3. Check `CHANGELOG.md` for recent changes
4. Run `python3 -m pytest tests/ -v` to confirm baseline health

## During Development
- Use Cursor's TODO tracking to manage multi-step tasks
- Only one task `in_progress` at a time
- Mark tasks `completed` immediately after finishing
- Break complex work into small, testable increments

## Session End Protocol
Before ending a session:
1. Run all tests and confirm they pass
2. Commit all changes with conventional commit messages
3. Update `CHANGELOG.md` if user-facing changes were made
4. Update status documentation with:
   - What was completed
   - What is in progress
   - Known issues or blockers
   - Next steps
5. Push to `develop` branch

## Status Update Format
```markdown
## Session Update — YYYY-MM-DD
### Completed
- [scope] Description of completed work
### In Progress
- [scope] Description of ongoing work
### Known Issues
- [scope] Description of issue and workaround
### Next Steps
- [scope] Description of planned work
```

## RFE Tracking
Requests for Enhancement from Confluence (page 6664028496) should be tracked as GitHub issues or referenced in development status when work begins.
